node.text: Enjoy and allow @ghazalmia fill your cup to the brim, as she spiritually and literally did mine. Maya brilliantly owns and shares her story and reminds us that we all have a part to play in making sure @refugees feel welcome. Thank you to UNHCR, the UN Refugee Agency, for setting up my favorite blind date. I can see clearly now the stereotypes we need to de-stigmatize so refugee stories can be rightfully supported and celebrated… Wanna join me in doing so? Of course you do, you humanity loving human. Learn more about their work and hear other refugee stories by clicking here: @refugees. Thank you in advance for the work we’ll do together bbs. #WorldRefugeeDay

node.title: Meet my lunch date, the magnetic @ghazalmia • Honoring World Refugee Day

node.text: This Party of One is now a party for all. I am beyond proud to present to you our baby, One of One. My clean skin care and makeup line with @cestmoibeauty, is now available for your indulgence. You deserve a daily celebration of your self-expression, and as a professional hype-woman, it’s my job to remind you of the powerful, playful potential in you. We lovingly created One of One to help you hype up the only you there will ever be. Welcome to your party, the pleasure is absolutely mine.

node.text: I'm Liza Koshy and I endorse hope. Be heard and VOTE TOMORROW, November 3rd. I had the honor of interviewing our Vice President/46th President Joe Biden in his final hours on the campaign trail. We talk about securing the future of America with the power of us Millennials and Gen Z, baby. We, the people, will create history this election day. We know what future we want, just choose it tomorrow. Make your plan to vote here: iwillvote.com. Stay joy ridin' with Biden and I here: www.joebiden.com. Thank you for watching, and I'll see you in our future, very soon.

node.title: A CUP O' JOE WITH JOE... BIDEN

node.text: I called up and pulled up with my friend/Queen, @carritwigg to continue the anti-racist conversation we forever need. Carri is the definition of a storyteller, and every chat with her is an eye-opener. So Karen, pull up, sit down, and become a Carri. She'll explain HOW to navigate these needed conversations at home, at work, in life and with love. Then check out @culturehousemedia, which focuses on the intersection of pop culture and politics in their brilliant productions. So don't be shy, talk some more! Continue the convo today.
